rComments: Great professor; lots of writing, but some of it is an automatic A; opportunities to revise and get a higher grades; not easy, but certainly not "hard"; I was dreading this class and ended up loving it. Take him for any English class you can; you will not be sorry.

Mr. Sellers is the top of the line in my book.We are not just a number in that class.He went over EVERYTHING with us and he was always there to answer questions. The best thing about him though was that he let us write about what we care about.
He was young and fun. He likes to do off the wall stuff (like dress up on halloween). I like his teaching style and hes really nice and fun.

Mr.Sellers is great.He is very helpful and clear with his assignments.I looked forward to going to his class.He also gives tons of opportunities to make sure you get an "A".Great teach, not boring at all!
OMG he is so hot!! I'd like to teach him a few things ; )

I love Mr. Sellers, my favoite teacher BY FARRR, he's amazing--and INCREDIBLY hot!! I left his class a WAYYY better writer than I was before plus I felt like I had a professor that i could talk to about anything. plus, he's HILARIOUS!
His class is my favorite this semester.  He does have you write a bunch but hes alot of fun!
